Image(corkMrak.jpg, Cork Oak in front of Mrak Hall, thumbnail)The scientific name of cork Oaks oak is Quercus suber. They are a drought tolerant species, which makes them especially suited to summers in Davis. The leaves are green, with a grayish underside. As the name implies, Cork Oaks bark is a source of cork, though most around here arent considered commercial quality.

For info on other local plants see Town Flora.
